about me

I'm an incoming graduate student at MIT pursuing a Masters in Engineering in computer science. I did my undergraduate studies at MIT and graduated in May 2020 with a major in computer science and a minor in music.

In my free time, I play vibraphone in the MIT Festival Jazz Ensemble. I also produce and host a radio show on WMBR (88.1 FM) called Bass Case (airs Saturdays at 12PM Eastern), and I work as one of two program directors for the station. You can find the playlists for every show I've produced here.
